"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93509","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-22","<p>The length of time each claimant has waited for the review and completion of a compensation claim under the War Pension and Armed Forces Compensation System since the inception of those schemes, in 1921 and 2005 respectively, is not available and can be provided only at disproportionate cost. However, the information below provides the average length of time taken to process claims under the War Pensions Scheme and Armed Forces Compensation Scheme in each year since 2009. Information before 2009 is not available.<br><br>WAR PENSIONS SCHEME<br>2009-10 45 working days<br>2010-11 39 working days<br>2011-12 51 working days<br>2012-13 82 working days<br>2013-14 110 working days<br>Year to date 103 working days<br><br>ARMED FORCES COMPENSATION SCHEME<br>2009-10 80 working days<br>2010-11 93 working days<br>2011-12 125 working days<br>2012-13 164 working days<br>2013-14 109 working days<br>Year to date 89 working days</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-22T16:19:35.5348827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93509/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93509/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93509/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","Armed Forces: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how long each claimant has waited for the review and completion of a compensation claim under the War Pension and the Armed Forces Compensation System Schemes since the inception of those schemes.","false","Biography information for Sandra Osborne","Ayr, Carrick and Cumnock","Sandra Osborne","210757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93510","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-23","<p>The Ministry of Defence has a robust plan to be enacted in the unlikely event that any of our troops contract Ebola.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-23T15:37:20.1264854Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93510/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93510/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93510/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93510/answer/previousversion/23148","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","Sierra Leone","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the Government has planned for incidents of Ebola infection amongst the 750 troops to be deployed in Sierra Leone.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","210737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93511","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-22","<p>All Armed Forces personnel deploying under Op GRITROCK are required to undertake specific training before deploying to Sierra Leone, to mitigate the risk that Ebola represents.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-22T16:24:11.0378017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93511/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93511/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93511/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93511/answer/previousversion/23149","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","Sierra Leone","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps the Government has taken to ensure that the 750 troops to be deployed to Sierra Leone have adequate training to minimise the risk of exposure to Ebola.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","210738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93512","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-21","<p>As I stated in my answer of 28 April 2014 (Official Report, columns 443-444W) the implications for Defence of changes made in 2011 to rehabilitation legislation relating to police cautions are complex and are the subject of advice to Minister being prepared by officials. <br><br>A total of five complaints arising from these changes were received from Service personnel in 2012. One was withdrawn and the remaining four complaints have been suspended pending the outome of Ministers' deliberation.<br><br>The initial exercise to determine the numbers of personnel affected by these legislative changes was undertaken to inform officials’ advice to Ministers. However, no detailed exercise to locate affected personnel has been undertaken.<br><br>When I have reached a decision, I will inform the House.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","210673 ; 210744","2014-10-21T16:37:43.7877495Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93512/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93512/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93512/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93512/answer/previousversion/23135","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","Armed Forces: Offenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many complaints his Department has received relating to punishments administered within the service justice or discipline system following the receipt of a police caution were stayed within the service complaints system; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","210743"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93513","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-21","<p>As I stated in my answer of 28 April 2014 (Official Report, columns 443-444W) the implications for Defence of changes made in 2011 to rehabilitation legislation relating to police cautions are complex and are the subject of advice to Minister being prepared by officials. <br><br>A total of five complaints arising from these changes were received from Service personnel in 2012. One was withdrawn and the remaining four complaints have been suspended pending the outome of Ministers' deliberation.<br><br>The initial exercise to determine the numbers of personnel affected by these legislative changes was undertaken to inform officials’ advice to Ministers. However, no detailed exercise to locate affected personnel has been undertaken.<br><br>When I have reached a decision, I will inform the House.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","210673 ; 210743","2014-10-21T16:37:43.5688952Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93513/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93513/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93513/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93513/answer/previousversion/23137","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","Armed Forces: Offenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what work Army Personnel Centre Glasgow has undertaken to identify and locate army personnel who have been disciplined after receiving a police caution; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","210744"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93514","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-20","<p>The Ministry of Defence is considering options for the future controlled humidity environment capability. These options have not been finalised but an assessment study is due to complete in 2015.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","210596","2014-10-20T16:24:53.1288343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93514/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93514/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93514/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","DSG Ashchurch","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the effect on options for the future delivery of controlled humidity environment capability of departmental decisions on land sale at MoD Ashchurch; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","210745"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93515","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-21","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 20 October 2014 to Questions UIN 210596 and UIN 210745, which can be found at the following link: http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=210596</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-10-21T16:34:15.6386759Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93515/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93515/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93515/answer","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93515/answer/previousversion/23150","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","DSG Ashchurch","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place a copy of all conditioning reports on the approximate costs of repairing Ashchurch subsequent to that commissioned from Babcock dated 3 February 2011 in the Library; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","210746"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93516","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-10","<p>In January 2011, the Defence Support Group (DSG) commissioned a study on behalf of the Ministry of Defence through their existing facilities' management provider, Babcock, to assess the maintenance work required to enable the DSG to safely undertake vehicle and equipment operation from specified buildings on the site at Ashchurch until 2016. The study, submitted in February 2011, estimated that the cost 'to make safe' the site for the five year period would be £2.863 million excluding VAT. The study report was passed to the Defence Infrastructure Organisation and Defence Equipment and Support for the recommendations to be acted upon.</p><p>I am unable to place a copy of the document in the Library as it's disclosure would prejudice commercial interests.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","210595","2014-11-10T17:34:09.531764Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93516/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93516/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93516/answer","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93516/answer/previousversion/23151","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","DSG Ashchurch","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what cost for repairing his Department's site at Ashchurch was estimated in the report commissioned by Babcock International dated 3 February 2011.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","210747"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93517","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-18","<p>We have decided to change both the Armed Forces Pension Scheme 75 (AFPS75) and the War Pension Scheme (WPS). The changes we have made will ensure that from 1 April 2015, widows, widowers and surviving civil partners of all members of the Armed Forces Pension Scheme will now retain their pensions for life, fulfilling the Government's ongoing commitment to the Armed Forces Covenant.</p><p>From 1 April 2015 the spouse or civil partner of all members of AFPS75 and any WPS widows will retain their pension for life if they have not already surrendered it due to remarriage or cohabitation.</p><p>For those who have already surrendered their pension due to remarriage or cohabitation, should that relationship end they can apply to have their pension restored for life.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","212562","2014-11-18T17:35:21.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93517/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93517/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93517/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93517/answer/previousversion/23793","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","Armed Forces: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will estimate the cost to the public purse of enabling all armed forces' widows to retain their pension in the event of later cohabiting or remarrying.","false","Biography information for Thomas Docherty","Dunfermline and West Fife","Thomas Docherty","210696"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93518","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-28","<p>Service inquiries were introduced on 1 October 2008, to replace the three single-Service systems of boards of inquiry. In the period from 1 October 2008 until 31 December 2012, the number of cases in which the death of a Service person was confirmed by a coroner (or the procurator fiscal for Scotland) as a suicide, and for which a service inquiry was held, is four.</p><p> </p><p>The number of cases in the Naval Service for which a board of inquiry was convened into a death confirmed as a suicide in the period from 1 January 2002 until 30 September 2008 is seven. Information about the number of boards of inquiry convened by either the Army or the RAF before October 2008 is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-28T16:41:03.7201051Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93518/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93518/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93518/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93518/answer/previousversion/23792","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","Armed Forces: Suicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many cases of suicide by serving armed forces personnel resulted in a full service enquiry between 2002 and 2012.","false","Biography information for Daniel Kawczynski","Shrewsbury and Atcham","Daniel Kawczynski","210678"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93519","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-22","<p>Book of Reference 3 – (Naval Personnel Management Regulations) is updated three times a year and is published online in full on the Royal Navy’s website at http://www.royalnavy.mod.uk/~/media/royal navy responsive/documents/useful resources/br 3/20140110-br3home-u.pdf</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-22T16:25:51.2435296Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93519/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93519/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93519/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","Navy: Personnel Management","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place in the Library a copy of BR3 - Naval Personnel Management.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","210675"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93520","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-22","<p>The Joint Service Publication 755 “Tri Service Positions and Assignment – Instructions” is currently being updated. It is expected that the latest version will be available by 30 November 2014. <br><br>Once it is available, I will place a copy in the Library of the House.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-22T16:20:03.5493741Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93520/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93520/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93520/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","Armed Forces: Publications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place in the Library a copy of Joint Service Publication 755.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","210676"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93521","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-22","<p>We have not undertaken any formal estimates on uprating the military compensation of injured veterans by whichever is the higher of earnings, inflation or 2.5 per cent. Our approach, increasing awards with reference to the Consumer Price Index, is in line with other public sector schemes, and consistent with the measure of inflation used by the Bank of England.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-22T16:31:01.5653587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93521/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93521/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93521/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","Armed Forces: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will estimate the cost to the public purse of uprating the military compensation of injured veterans by whichever is the higher of earnings, inflation or 2.5 per cent.","false","Biography information for Thomas Docherty","Dunfermline and West Fife","Thomas Docherty","210698"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93522","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-22","<p>The provision of mental health services for veterans is a matter for the Department of Health and therefore no such estimate has been undertaken. <br><br>You will be aware of the announcement made by my right hon. Friend the Deputy Prime Minister on 8 October 2014, announcing new waiting time standards from April 2015 for the treatment of mental health conditions by NHS England. I also understand that the Scottish Government has set a target for the NHS in Scotland to deliver a maximum 18 week wait from referral to treatment for Psychological therapies from December 2014.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-22T16:20:54.0431007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93522/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93522/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93522/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","Veterans: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will estimate the cost to the public purse of guaranteeing veterans with mental health problems evidence-based treatment provided by practitioners with an understanding of veterans' needs within 18 weeks of referral.","false","Biography information for Thomas Docherty","Dunfermline and West Fife","Thomas Docherty","210699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93523","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-22","<p>The estimated cost of the Early Service Leavers enhanced support under the current Career Transition Partnership (CTP) contract from October 2013 to 30 September 2015 is £1 million.<br><br>The estimated cost of continuing this provision and the employment support to spouses (a new requirement) in the CTP contract beyond 1 October 2015 is not yet available as the bidders have yet to submit their tenders.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-22T16:21:26.070819Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93523/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93523/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93523/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","Veterans: Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will estimate the cost to the public purse of including spouses and early service leavers in the resettlement support provided by the Careers Transition Partnership.","false","Biography information for Thomas Docherty","Dunfermline and West Fife","Thomas Docherty","210700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93524","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-22","<p>The provision of hearing aids for veterans is a matter for the Department of Health (DH) and therefore no such estimate has been undertaken. For veterans of a working age, priority National Health Service (NHS) treatment and access to clinically appropriate digital aids where hearing problems are due to service is already best practice across the United Kingdom. For veterans with hearing loss just below the compensation threshold I have written to my Ministerial colleagues responsible for health in England, Wales, Scotland and Northern Ireland and have their agreement in principle that these individuals should be able to access NHS supplied digital aids. The DH has advised recently that the NHS England strategy on hearing aids is currently out for consultation with a view to sign off early next year.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-22T16:30:16.7148093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93524/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93524/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93524/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","Veterans: Hearing Aids","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will estimate the cost to the public purse of ensuring that (a) all veterans with service-related hearing problems are able to have their MoD-issued hearing aids serviced and replaced at no cost and (b) working-age veterans can access higher grade hearing aids including in-the-ear aids.","false","Biography information for Thomas Docherty","Dunfermline and West Fife","Thomas Docherty","210697"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93525","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-24","<p>As of 12 November, the UK has conducted 16 strikes in Iraq from Tornado and Reaper aircraft using Paveway IV bombs and Hellfire and Brimstone missiles against a range of targets including vehicles, troop positions, heavy weapons and facilities. Assessments of these strikes have shown that they hit and destroyed their targets successfully. An accurate count of ISIL casualties cannot always be made in this type of environment. All air strikes are conducted in accordance with the Rules of Engagement and international humanitarian law. Careful selection, approval and close observation of targets prior to a strike and the use of precision guided munitions minimises collateral damage and the potential for civilian casualties. To date we have not received any reports of civilian casualties, which is supported by our own analysis of each attack.</p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-11-24T16:55:27.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93525/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93525/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93525/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93525/answer/previousversion/23776","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","Iraq","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many targets the Royal Air Force has hit in Iraq since 26 September 2014; how many casualties have occurred as a result; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","210712"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93526","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-21","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) is still undertaking studies into the future of the site at MOD Ashchurch. Once all functions currently undertaken at MOD Ashchurch have been relocated to other facilities, appropriate supporting documentation will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","210795 ; 210802","2014-10-21T16:36:55.9554406Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93526/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93526/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93526/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","DSG Ashchurch","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place copies of all reviews carried out by his Department into the phased site closure of MoD Ashchurch in the Library; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","210722"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93527","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-07","<p>A list of all Ministry of Defence (MOD) Category A, B and C Projects is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p>A list of Category A, B and C Projects for Equipment (including Information, Communications and Technology but excluding Equipment Support Programmes) and Infrastructure is held and is provided in the tables attached. I am, however, withholding a number of project titles for the purpose of safeguarding national security, and that their release would, or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p><p>Category A, B and C Equipment Projects are defined as those valued in excess of £400 million; between £100 and £400 million; and between £20 and £100 million respectively. The tables contain only those projects at the post Initial Gate/pre-In-Service Date stage.</p><p>Infrastructure projects categories A and C are defined as those valued in excess of £100 million; and between £10 and £100 million respectively. There is no Category B for Infrastructure Projects.</p><p>Further information on major projects throughout Government, including Defence, can be found in the Cabinet Office Government Major Projects Portfolio. This is available on the gov.uk website at the following link: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/major-projects-authority-annual-report-2014</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-11-07T14:14:25.2372537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93527/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93527/answer","Equipment Projects.doc  HOC 210645.doc","Infrastructure Projects","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93527/answer","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93527/answer/previousversion/23769","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","Defence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will list his Department's (a) category A, (b) category B and (c) category C defence projects.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","210645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93528","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-22","<p>The information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost as category D defence equipment projects are up to £20 million and defence infrastructure projects are up to £10 million in value. Category D projects are also within the discretion of each Command under the delegated model of defence transformation.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-10-22T16:19:03.3124695Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93528/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93528/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93528/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","Defence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will list his Department's category D defence projects.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","210646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93529","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-22","<p>This will be considered in consultation with our partners in the US Coast Guard.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-10-22T16:17:31.0237486Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93529/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93529/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93529/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-15","Navy: US Coast Guard","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place in the Library a copy of the Memorandum of Understanding on US coast guard sailors serving on Royal Navy warships signed by the US Coast Guard Commandant and Admiral Sir George Zambellas in July 2014.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","210648"
