"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93129","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-21","<p>The Defence Clothing Team, part of Defence Equipment &amp; Support, is responsible for providing all waterproof clothing under the Waterproof Garments Contract to the Regular Forces, Army Reservists, Ministry Of Defence (MOD) Police and Guards, and Cadets. <br>Since March 2011 waterproof clothing has been supplied to the MOD, under the Waterproof Garments Contract, by ITURRI SA. The previous contractor, awarded the contract in March 2007, was Thistle Garments Ltd. <br>The advert and requirement for the new Waterproof Garments Contract, commonly known as the Taped Seam Contract, is due to be published in the Official Journal for the European Union (OJEU) and the MOD Defence Contracts Bulletin (DCB) in November. It will give potential providers details on how to express an interest in bidding for the requirement. Once the contract has been awarded, a contract award notice will be published in the OJEU and DCB. This contract award notice will provide details of the winning bidder and the value of the contract.<br><br></p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","210292 ; 210293 ; 210294 ; 210575","2014-10-21T16:33:12.0887327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93129/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93129/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93129/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-14","Armed Forces: Uniforms","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether an invitation to tender has been put out for military waterproof clothing contract.","false","Biography information for Alison Seabeck","Plymouth, Moor View","Alison Seabeck","210295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93130","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-21","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) fully understands the importance of this development in Wales, and is therefore working with the Welsh Government to ensure the success of the transition to a wholly civil operation by 2019. However, since the private companies based at MOD St Athan are clients of the Welsh Government, the only relationships which they hold are with the Welsh Government.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-21T16:35:20.9097498Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93130/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93130/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93130/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-14","MOD St Athan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will assess his Department's relationship with private companies based at MOD St Athan.","false","Biography information for David T. C. Davies","Monmouth","David T. C. Davies","210296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93131","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-25","<p>Since August 2014 the UK has gifted urgent lethal military support to the Peshmerga in the form of heavy machine guns and ammunition to Kurdish forces at the request of the Iraqi Government in Baghdad.</p><p>Non-lethal items such as Halal rations, sleeping bags, body armour and helmets have also been supplied. In addition, we have assisted with the delivery of munitions and equipment on behalf of other Coalition members.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-11-25T16:49:40.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93131/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93131/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93131/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93131/answer/previousversion/23533","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-14","Kurds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the military resources which have been provided to Kurdish forces by the UK in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","210378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93132","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-20","<p>Private companies are afforded the same airfield hours that are available to all users. Currently, while the new airfield contractor completes work-up training, the airfield is available for take-offs and landings from Monday to Friday between 9 am and 5 pm and, with 24 hours notice, on Saturday and Sunday from 9 am to 5 pm. Arrangements to operate outside these hours may be made, subject to manpower availability, by prior request. The Welsh Government's intent is to provide airfield opening hours of 9 am until 5 pm every day of the week, from December 2014.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-20T16:19:33.5828503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93132/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93132/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93132/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93132/answer/previousversion/22773","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-14","MOD St Athan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, during what hours MOD St Athan is available for use by private companies.","false","Biography information for David T. C. Davies","Monmouth","David T. C. Davies","210321"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93133","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-27","<p>There were no visits made by Defence Ministers to the Torbay Constituency in the last 12 months to 14 October 2014.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-27T16:52:00.1158446Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93133/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93133/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93133/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93133/answer/previousversion/23537","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-14","Torbay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many visits were made by Ministers of his Department to Torbay constituency in the 12 months to 14 October 2014; whom the invitation for each such visit was issued by; and what the cost to the public purse was of each such visit.","false","Biography information for Mr Adrian Sanders","Torbay","Mr Adrian Sanders","210476"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93134","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-21","<p>Officials from the Ministry of Defence and the Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office have communicated with US officials in face-to-face meetings and by correspondence to agree the terms of the Amending Agreement to renew the 1958 Mutual Defence Agreement. The Amending Agreement was signed, subject to ratification, by the UK and US Governments on 22 July 2014 and laid before Parliament on 16 October 2014.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2014-10-21T16:45:03.4071935Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93134/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93134/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93134/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-14","USA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what communications (a) he and (b) officials in his Department have had with his US counterpart or US defense department officials in 2014 regarding the extension of the 1958 US-UK Mutual Defense Agreement on atomic energy matters.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","210436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93135","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-21","<p>The Maritime Support Delivery Framework contracts will sustain around 7,500 jobs in total, with around 4,000 of these jobs at Her Majesty’s Naval Base (HMNB) Devonport, a further 1,500 at HMNB Clyde and more than 2,000 at HMNB Portsmouth.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2014-10-21T16:49:12.4284048Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93135/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93135/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93135/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-14","Devonport Dockyard","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the effect of the Maritime Support Delivery Framework will be on employment levels at HMNB Devonport.","false","Biography information for Oliver Colvile","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Oliver Colvile","210446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93136","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-27","<p>None of the munitions supplied to UK Forces for use over Iraq contains depleted uranium; there are no UK forces operating in Syria. There are no plans to issue depleted uranium weapons to UK forces operating over Iraq.</p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-27T16:47:46.6438515Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93136/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93136/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93136/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93136/answer/previousversion/23529","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-14","Depleted Uranium","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his policy is on the use of depleted uranium by UK armed forces operating in Iraq and Syria.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","210447"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93137","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-20","<p>As the Minister responsible for welfare issues, I met the Chief Executive of the Army Families Federation on 14 October 2014 to discuss Army housing. I will also be speaking about this and a variety of other issues at the Army Families Federation Conference on 21 October.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-10-20T16:59:12.9739775Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93137/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93137/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93137/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-14","Army Families Federation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he last met the Armies Families Federation; and what was discussed at that meeting.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","210398"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93138","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-20","<p>The Government has been clear that dealing with this threat will take time and patience. Our intention is to provide support to the Iraqi government while we believe it to be both needed and the Iraqi government still requests it. The UK airstrikes and other military support shows the UK will play its part in standing against ISIL.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-11-20T16:56:30.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93138/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93138/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93138/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93138/answer/previousversion/23530","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-14","Iraq","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the length of time that UK military forces will be engaged in Iraq.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","210383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93139","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-10-27","<p>There are currently around 20 UK Armed Forces Personnel performing various non-combat roles in Northern Iraq. The majority of this number deployed before 26 September 2014.</p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-10-27T16:47:01.653785Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93139/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93139/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93139/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93139/answer/previousversion/23531","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-10-14","Iraq","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many British forces have been deployed on the ground in northern Iraq since 26 September 2014.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","210435"
